message: "If you use this protocol or build on it, please cite it as below."
title: "Peer-Worker Convergence: a protocol for running multiple AI coding sessions on one repo without divergence"
abstract: "A coordination protocol for running multiple AI coding sessions on a shared git repository, with long-lived worker branches converging through a canonical main via session-start and session-end ceremonies (α/β/γ rules) and a precision-target side-branch ceremony for concurrent convergence."
